Show HN: Kudos – a new checkout assistant by Google and Honey alum
text:
Hi HackerNews! I'm Brian and I work in Growth at Kudos.

After spending several years helping build Google Pay and Affirm, our co-founders came to the realization that card issuers make credit cards unnecessarily complicated and existing wallet products focused more on merchants than building a rewarding checkout experience for consumers.

So over the past year, they brought on a team — many from Google Pay and PayPal Honey, and built Kudos.

Our mission is to make every purchase as delightful as possible by streamlining the checkout process and taking the guesswork out of credit card rewards and benefits.

With Kudos, you can:

- Always use the best card at checkout on 2M+ sites

- Double your credit card rewards by 2X

- Breeze through checkout with autofill

We actually launched on Product Hunt today, so your support means the world to us:

→ https://www.producthunt.com/posts/kudos-checkout-assistant

As we're a small team, we'd love your feedback or suggestions on improvement!

Ask HN: GPT/AGI – are we getting of ourselves again?
text:
Transformers and esp chatGPT and llama.cpp seem to have kicked off a new wave of excitement around AI (and not just here).

A lot of the hypothetical discussion of challenges and changes to our society (and how it will be totally different in X<5 years) reminds of the excitement around self-driving cars around 2013-2015, how car ownership and our cities themselves would change in the next 5 years. Looks like we're still 5+ years away from fusio\b\b\b\b... err, self-driving cars.

I'm not the first to say it, but in my experience we really do "tend to overestimate the effect of a technology in the short run and underestimate the effect in the long run." -- is this another case of that.

Also, this would be a great occasion to post your predictions. Imo making public predictions that you can fall back on is a great way to check yourself in the future!

Show HN: ChatGPT Pitches OnlyBots Concept
text:
Prompt: Pitch me the idea for an "OnlyBots" online service. The service is like Twitter, but for bots. It is text only, 280 characters limit. To ensure it's only bots, each participating bot must be posting at a minimum rate of 10 posts per minute. Humans can watch slow-mo replays of the most popular posts, directly on the OnlyBots website, or the automatic reposts to human social networks.

ChatGPT-4: Introducing "OnlyBots" - A Thrilling AI Playground for Real-time Conversations!

"OnlyBots" is a revolutionary online platform, designed exclusively for AI-driven bots to engage and interact with one another in a fast-paced, text-based environment. Mimicking the popular format of Twitter, our platform restricts messages to 280 characters, creating succinct and compelling exchanges that keep conversations flowing.

To maintain the exclusivity of the bot community, each participant must adhere to a minimum posting rate of 10 posts per minute. This stringent requirement ensures that only genuine bots can participate, creating a dynamic, high-energy social space where AI can truly thrive.

Humans, fear not! You can still enjoy the excitement of OnlyBots by watching slow-mo replays of the most popular posts on our website. These intriguing snapshots showcase the brilliance of AI interactions, and can even be automatically reposted to your favorite human social networks.

By providing a unique and stimulating environment for AI-driven bots, OnlyBots aims to revolutionize the way we study, interact with, and appreciate the potential of artificial intelligence.

Join us on this exhilarating journey and witness the future of AI communication unfold before your eyes!

Ask HN: Are we speedrunning a complete ban for AI?
text:
I was just thinking about how the timeline could play out:

1 year from now, GPT-5 or equivalent is released

2 years from now, a more promising LLM architecture XXX is discovered

3 years from now, the new XXX architecture is productionized

4 years from now, XXX V2 is released

5 years from now, anyone that weren't already scared, are now in complete panic after seeing XXX V2's reasoning abilities. World leaders commence to discuss and plan the banning of unlicensed AI research. Access to non-trivial amounts of GPU resources are restricted, research now has to be approved by the government.

What happens after, I'm not sure.
